{{Quote|No matter how technologically advanced moviemaking instruments have become, they remain tools. And as tools, they will always need artists to wield them, and their creative visions to lead the way. To us, there is no greater example of such an artist than John Knoll. Whatever the problem we throw at him, he'll never fail to come up with a solution that not only meets the technical requirements or limitations of the project, but also makes sense within the overall storytelling. Hand the impossible to John, and he'll crack it.|[[Rick McCallum]]|<ref name="SW">{{SWArchive|url=episode-i/bts/production/f19990602/index.html|text=At First Glance}}</ref>}}
'''John Knoll''' is Chief Creative Officer/Senior Visual Effects Supervisor of [[Industrial Light & Magic]], having been promoted to that position on [[May 23]], [[2013]], after serving as the company's visual effects supervisor. He joined ILM in [[1986]].<ref name="Insider">{{InsiderCite|218|Speaking Volumes}}</ref>

Knoll is an [[Wikipedia:Academy Award|Academy Award]] winner, and has been nominated five times overall for his work on visual effects. In addition to his extensive visual-effects work on the [[Prequel trilogy|prequels]], Knoll created the [[opening crawl]]s for all three films on his personal computer.<ref name="SWArchive-Episode III: How It Begins">{{SWArchive|url=episode-iii/bts/production/f20050126/index.html|text=Episode III: How It Begins}}</ref>

He made cameo appearances as [[Rya Kirsch]] in [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|Episode I]] and as [[Tannon Praji]] and the [[Coruscant Rescue Ops|Coruscant firefighter pilot]] in [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|Episode III]].

His first book, ''[[Creating the Worlds of Star Wars: 365 Days]]'', was released on [[October 1]], [[2005]].

He also worked with [[George Lucas]] on the [[1988]] film [[Willow (film)|''Willow'']], on which he served as ILM's animation camera operator.

In [[2016]], Knoll announced that the film ''[[Rogue One: A Star Wars Story]]'' is based on an unproduced script that he wrote for the [[Star Wars: Underworld|''Star Wars'' live-action TV show]]. He is also one of the members of the [[Intellectual Property Development Group]].<ref name="Art Last Jedi">''[[The Art of Star Wars: The Last Jedi]]''</ref> Knoll worked in creating ''[[Star Wars: The Mandalorian]]'', making a motion control rig used to film shots of the ''[[Razor Crest]]''.<ref name="Insider" />

Besides his film work, he co-created the digital image-processing program [[Wikipedia:Adobe Photoshop|Adobe Photoshop]].

